{
  "id": "tom_tilt_spy",
  "thesis": "Turn-of-month seasonal tilt on SPY: hold SPY at all times but apply a small calendar-locked overweight during the turn-of-month window (last trading day of the prior month through trading day +3, weighted toward days 0/+1), funded by a small underweight parked in a defensive TLT/GLD/HYG inverse-vol blend the rest of the month. Harvests the institutional-flow TOM anomaly (payroll/401k inflows, dividend reinvestment, month-end rebalancing) as a mild oscillation rather than an in/out switch, so it keeps the equity risk premium and only rebalances ~twice a month. Window is fixed from theory, not fit; fully-invested rotation with no cash drag.",
